cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with pattern classification and the derivation of bounds under minimal learnability hypotheses. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the handling of capacity measures, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of combinatorial and structural results suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of support vector machines, which is a popular technique in the field of signal processing and image analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the characterization of the dependence of the bound on the three basic parameters suggests a connection to neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
